nodes.title: Positive Prompt
widgets_values: Slow motion frame interpolation of a man performing a series of kicks and a straight back flip at the end.

Make sure to use "slow motion" in the prompt if you have a lot of keyframes and are planing to control the animation very precisely so it interprets the video as slow motion since it's using 30fps for the video output but WAN2.1 native is 16fps.

If the animation appears too jittery it's likely because WAN isn't treating it as a slow motion. Try to fiddle with the prompt until you get it to take it in as slow motion which should result in smooth animations.

For the future a slow motion Lora would be very helpful

If VRAM constrained lower the megapixels slider until it fits

480p = 0.41
720p = 0.92
